What a great venue.

00:00:39.176 --> 00:00:40.436
This is really great.

00:00:40.586 --> 00:00:41.956
Thanks for coming today.

00:00:41.956 --> 00:00:45.236
It's been a long day, but we've
got some really great stuff

00:00:45.236 --> 00:00:45.636
for you.

00:00:46.086 --> 00:00:47.266
So I want to welcome you

00:00:47.266 --> 00:00:50.896
to the 15th Apple
Design Award Ceremony.

00:00:51.326 --> 00:00:54.266
And we've got a ton of
great winners this evening.

00:00:54.576 --> 00:00:58.146
And we'd like to, of course,
recognize their great work.

00:00:58.806 --> 00:01:02.136
The Apple Design Awards are all
about recognizing great work

00:01:02.136 --> 00:01:03.636
by people in this community.

00:01:03.826 --> 00:01:08.556
And this is the moment when many
of you -- well, many of you --

00:01:08.666 --> 00:01:10.716
some of you get to take home one

00:01:10.716 --> 00:01:12.196
of the Apple Design
Award Trophies,

00:01:12.586 --> 00:01:15.536
which everyone wants one.

00:01:15.656 --> 00:01:18.596
And so we'll see who
gets one tonight.

00:01:19.566 --> 00:01:22.026
But to start things off, I
just want to set a little bit

00:01:22.026 --> 00:01:25.086
of context for the apps that
are going to win tonight.

00:01:26.156 --> 00:01:29.386
The App Store opened
eight years ago.

00:01:29.386 --> 00:01:32.636
In fact, next month it'll
be exactly eight years old.

00:01:32.636 --> 00:01:35.126
And it was on July 10th of 2008.

00:01:35.236 --> 00:01:39.556
And in those eight
years, apps took off.

00:01:39.556 --> 00:01:40.496
Right? They've taken off.

00:01:40.496 --> 00:01:43.126
And today, we heard 2
million apps on the App Store.

00:01:43.126 --> 00:01:45.556
But if we just go
back for a moment

00:01:45.556 --> 00:01:48.736
to those first days,
it was pretty crazy.

00:01:48.736 --> 00:01:51.366
I mean, it all started off
with the iPhone, right?

00:01:51.366 --> 00:01:54.496
And we all remember
the first TV ads.

00:01:55.146 --> 00:01:56.706
They were 30-second slots.

00:01:57.446 --> 00:01:59.636
And in those 30-second
slots, you had five

00:01:59.636 --> 00:02:01.316
or six apps that were featured.

00:02:02.156 --> 00:02:05.436
And so each app had five
seconds to audition with you,

00:02:05.436 --> 00:02:07.766
the customer -- with
you, the audience.

00:02:08.726 --> 00:02:10.446
And to make an impression

00:02:10.645 --> 00:02:12.556
in five seconds is
a pretty big deal.

00:02:12.556 --> 00:02:18.016
But what happened in those ads
was people would watch the ads

00:02:18.016 --> 00:02:20.286
and they would stop
everything that they were doing

00:02:20.286 --> 00:02:22.626
and they would pay attention to
the app that was being shown.

00:02:22.626 --> 00:02:23.866
And within five seconds,

00:02:23.866 --> 00:02:25.746
they would have decided
whether it mattered to them

00:02:25.746 --> 00:02:28.816
and if they were going to go
and download it or buy it.

00:02:28.816 --> 00:02:30.266
And I think that's
pretty impressive.

00:02:30.266 --> 00:02:34.826
And those apps -- basically, it
was those TV ads and those apps

00:02:35.026 --> 00:02:38.356
that created the phrase,
"There's an app for that."

00:02:38.356 --> 00:02:39.796
And that phrase was born.

00:02:40.376 --> 00:02:43.086
And it was during
that time way early

00:02:43.086 --> 00:02:45.286
on that we saw enormous
creativity.

00:02:45.286 --> 00:02:47.646
I mean, we didn't have
this thing before.

00:02:47.756 --> 00:02:48.476
iPhone was out.

00:02:48.476 --> 00:02:49.946
We had this SDK.

00:02:49.946 --> 00:02:51.106
We didn't have that before.

00:02:51.106 --> 00:02:52.856
And we saw enormous creativity.

00:02:53.006 --> 00:02:55.996
We saw great games,
really useful

00:02:55.996 --> 00:02:57.806
and very valuable utilities,

00:02:58.086 --> 00:03:00.536
some pretty incredible
augmented reality,

00:03:00.976 --> 00:03:03.086
and lots of other great stuff,

00:03:03.086 --> 00:03:05.056
much of which was
really groundbreaking.

00:03:05.606 --> 00:03:11.166
And then, two years later,
the iPad was introduced.

00:03:11.166 --> 00:03:13.376
And it was introduced
not far from here

00:03:13.376 --> 00:03:15.486
at the Yerba Buena
Center of the Arts.

00:03:15.486 --> 00:03:16.936
And I remember that day.

00:03:16.936 --> 00:03:18.656
It was an incredible day.

00:03:19.156 --> 00:03:22.106
But when the iPad
arrived in 2010,

00:03:22.306 --> 00:03:24.606
it brought a whole
new wave of apps.

00:03:25.116 --> 00:03:28.376
And these were apps that
stopped us in our tracks.

00:03:28.376 --> 00:03:32.186
I mean these were apps that,
when we first saw them,

00:03:32.186 --> 00:03:35.186
they caused us to
pause and to be amazed

00:03:35.546 --> 00:03:36.846
at what could be
done on this device.

00:03:36.846 --> 00:03:39.816
And then we had universal
apps coming

00:03:39.816 --> 00:03:42.576
and bringing functionality
from iPad back to iPhone,

00:03:42.576 --> 00:03:44.816
and the experience of all
of the apps got better.

00:03:45.666 --> 00:03:50.646
And all of these apps early on
changed the way that we taught.

00:03:51.196 --> 00:03:53.936
They changed the way that
people learned with iPad.

00:03:54.376 --> 00:03:57.166
They changed the way that we
shared, that we connected,

00:03:57.166 --> 00:04:00.556
that we worked, and that
we spent our day getting

00:04:00.556 --> 00:04:01.536
things done.

00:04:02.376 --> 00:04:04.336
These were transformational
apps.

00:04:05.226 --> 00:04:06.286
And then more recently,

00:04:06.286 --> 00:04:10.436
Apple Watch was introduced,
and Apple TV.

00:04:10.436 --> 00:04:13.526
And with each of these, we
saw a new wave of apps coming.

00:04:15.106 --> 00:04:17.266
And so now, as you've
heard several times today,

00:04:17.576 --> 00:04:20.016
we've got four platforms
for you.

00:04:20.616 --> 00:04:21.896
And this is amazing.

00:04:22.196 --> 00:04:24.836
I mean, for me, being
at Apple 16 years,

00:04:24.836 --> 00:04:26.496
I remember when it
was just the Mac

00:04:26.806 --> 00:04:29.246
and there was some
great work going on.

00:04:29.886 --> 00:04:34.776
And then everything took
off, and now the Mac is part

00:04:34.776 --> 00:04:36.416
of that whole ecosystem.

00:04:36.416 --> 00:04:39.046
And there's a tremendous
opportunity for you

00:04:39.246 --> 00:04:40.746
with these four platforms.

00:04:41.136 --> 00:04:43.776
And we're starting to see
some really great work

00:04:43.776 --> 00:04:46.036
from developers on
these four platforms,

00:04:46.656 --> 00:04:48.556
and a few of those will
be honored here tonight.

00:04:49.856 --> 00:04:53.156
Now, tonight's winners
have created apps that are,

00:04:53.326 --> 00:04:57.216
once again, that set a
benchmark for excellence.

00:04:58.226 --> 00:05:01.726
And they set a benchmark
for excellence in usability,

00:05:03.176 --> 00:05:11.586
excellence in design, excellent
innovation, and excellence

00:05:11.586 --> 00:05:12.846
in technology adoption.

00:05:13.526 --> 00:05:16.286
And if you've been part of
the Apple Design Awards before

00:05:16.286 --> 00:05:18.036
or ever heard me speak, you know

00:05:18.036 --> 00:05:20.816
that that's not all
there is to a great app.

00:05:21.026 --> 00:05:24.006
There's even more that we
look for in winning apps.

00:05:24.446 --> 00:05:27.086
We're always looking for
whether the app is compelling

00:05:27.086 --> 00:05:29.176
and leaves a great
first impression.

00:05:29.856 --> 00:05:32.476
We're always looking for
whether an app is engaging,

00:05:32.716 --> 00:05:35.646
meaning it draws you
in and keeps you there,

00:05:35.646 --> 00:05:38.096
and then gets you coming
back again and again.

00:05:38.706 --> 00:05:40.166
That's a big challenge for apps.

00:05:41.296 --> 00:05:43.576
We look for apps that are
enabling, that allow you

00:05:43.576 --> 00:05:45.866
to do things you
could never do before.

00:05:46.346 --> 00:05:49.046
We're looking for
state-of-the-art apps of course.

00:05:49.136 --> 00:05:51.126
We're looking for
accessible apps.

00:05:51.126 --> 00:05:52.976
We're looking for
localized apps.

00:05:52.976 --> 00:05:55.606
Because accessible and
localized apps mean

00:05:55.606 --> 00:05:58.326
that those apps are available
to an even wider audience

00:05:58.726 --> 00:06:02.026
than they were prior to being
accessible and localized.

00:06:02.026 --> 00:06:04.556
And so there's a lot
of stuff that we look

00:06:04.626 --> 00:06:07.696
for in winning apps, and these
are just some of the things

00:06:07.856 --> 00:06:09.226
that we watch for
in winning apps.

00:06:09.956 --> 00:06:11.346
So let's get started.

00:06:11.346 --> 00:06:15.036
Let's start with apps that
were written by students.

00:06:15.956 --> 00:06:21.526
So you've heard today that we
had 350 scholarship winners this

00:06:21.526 --> 00:06:23.886
year at WWDC, which
is a record number.

00:06:24.536 --> 00:06:27.296
And these folks, these
students, had to submit an app.

00:06:27.606 --> 00:06:29.226
As part of the scholarship
process,

00:06:29.516 --> 00:06:32.506
they had to submit an app that
was either written explicitly

00:06:32.506 --> 00:06:35.156
for the scholarship
selection process,

00:06:35.156 --> 00:06:37.066
or they could just
tell us about an app

00:06:37.116 --> 00:06:38.916
that they had already
developed and put on --

00:06:38.916 --> 00:06:41.036
that was already
on the App Store.

00:06:41.036 --> 00:06:42.576
And we looked through
all these apps

00:06:42.576 --> 00:06:44.436
and we found some
pretty cool stuff.

00:06:45.306 --> 00:06:47.906
So tonight we want to
award two student winners.

00:06:48.556 --> 00:06:52.966
And the first is Linum by
Joaquin Vila from Mexico.

00:06:53.516 --> 00:07:11.896
[ Applause ]

00:07:12.396 --> 00:07:12.736
>> Thanks so much.

00:07:12.786 --> 00:07:13.316
>> You're welcome.

00:07:14.516 --> 00:07:20.846
