00:07:21.346 --> 00:07:25.526
All right, so Joaquin
started developing this app

00:07:25.776 --> 00:07:29.106
after he had applied for a
job at a local game developer,

00:07:29.106 --> 00:07:30.426
and that hadn't worked out.

00:07:30.666 --> 00:07:32.976
And he decided after
that that, like,

00:07:33.466 --> 00:07:35.676
he could just do
this on his own.

00:07:35.796 --> 00:07:37.536
He didn't need to work
for no other developer.

00:07:37.656 --> 00:07:41.846
So he decided to write his own
app, get it on the App Store.

00:07:42.146 --> 00:07:45.556
And I'd like to show
you this app.

00:07:45.676 --> 00:07:47.546
And before I do, I just wanted

00:07:47.546 --> 00:07:52.036
to say Joaquin was a 2015
Scholarship Winner last year

00:07:52.126 --> 00:07:53.746
at WWDC, so probably
learned a lot

00:07:53.746 --> 00:07:56.646
about what you used
in the app last year.

00:07:56.646 --> 00:08:00.726
And he's also super active in
the local developer community

00:08:00.726 --> 00:08:02.146
in many of the meetups
in his hometown.

00:08:02.146 --> 00:08:07.156
All right, so I'm just going to
show you this on this screen.

00:08:07.156 --> 00:08:09.616
So what you're seeing here
is Linum is a puzzle game

00:08:09.796 --> 00:08:12.036
where the goal is
to complete levels

00:08:12.036 --> 00:08:13.606
in the fewest moves possible.

00:08:13.606 --> 00:08:17.566
And what you're trying to do is
take these line nodes and lines

00:08:17.566 --> 00:08:21.086
and pivot them around to connect
with nodes to solve the puzzles.

00:08:21.556 --> 00:08:23.396
And as the number
of nodes increases,

00:08:23.696 --> 00:08:26.246
complex puzzles challenge
even the best players.

00:08:26.246 --> 00:08:30.346
And the beauty of Linum
is its simplicity.

00:08:30.346 --> 00:08:33.035
It's got a clean UI and
a simple set of rules.

00:08:33.035 --> 00:08:35.736
And with a smart
implementation of touch

00:08:36.046 --> 00:08:37.986
and approachable
progression system,

00:08:38.356 --> 00:08:41.966
terrific overall presentation
and use of Apple technologies,

00:08:42.405 --> 00:08:45.816
Linum is without doubt an
Apple Design Award Winner

00:08:45.816 --> 00:08:46.306
for a student.

00:08:46.306 --> 00:08:46.926
So, congratulations.

00:08:47.516 --> 00:08:56.606
[ Applause ]

00:08:57.106 --> 00:08:57.436
All right.

00:08:57.436 --> 00:09:01.136
