development challenge earlier

00:09:37.676 --> 00:09:38.146
this year.

00:09:38.146 --> 00:09:39.106
And it was at that event

00:09:39.106 --> 00:09:41.906
that they started
working on this game.

00:09:41.906 --> 00:09:43.656
And Josh is the programmer.

00:09:43.656 --> 00:09:44.226
Is it Josh?

00:09:44.366 --> 00:09:44.516
>> Yeah.

00:09:44.516 --> 00:09:45.656
>> Yeah, Josh is the programmer.

00:09:45.876 --> 00:09:47.276
Patrick is the designer.

00:09:47.276 --> 00:09:50.946
And Erik is the guy who created
the soundtrack for the game

00:09:51.226 --> 00:09:53.826
but also kind of kept you
guys on track, you know,

00:09:53.826 --> 00:09:55.126
in terms of development.

00:09:55.356 --> 00:10:00.166
So let me just show you
this game for a minute.

00:10:00.216 --> 00:10:05.516
So Dividr is this fun and
addicting 2D arcade game.

00:10:05.516 --> 00:10:09.046
And it makes use of 3D
touch of variant pressure

00:10:09.316 --> 00:10:13.856
to move the control
squares in and out depending

00:10:13.856 --> 00:10:15.606
on the pressure that
you apply to the screen.

00:10:15.896 --> 00:10:18.086
So the more pressure you
apply, the further out they go.

00:10:18.316 --> 00:10:20.316
The lighter on you are,
the closer in they go.

00:10:20.426 --> 00:10:24.546
And you're basically avoiding
these obstacles on screen.

00:10:25.026 --> 00:10:27.696
It's simple and compelling,
written entirely

00:10:27.696 --> 00:10:29.856
in Swift, supports Game Center.

00:10:30.126 --> 00:10:32.926
And it was, without a
doubt, a great choice

00:10:33.036 --> 00:10:34.846
for an Apple Design
Award this evening.

00:10:35.416 --> 00:10:35.976
Congratulations.

