00:11:28.936 --> 00:11:29.916
from New York City.

00:11:30.516 --> 00:11:41.516
[ Applause ]

00:11:42.516 --> 00:11:49.546
[ Music ]

00:11:50.046 --> 00:11:50.476
Congratulations.

00:11:50.476 --> 00:11:51.996
Great job, guys.

00:11:52.996 --> 00:11:55.636
Great to meet you.

00:11:56.516 --> 00:12:01.746
[ Music ]

00:12:02.246 --> 00:12:05.736
All right, so Frame.io is a
video collaboration platform

00:12:05.736 --> 00:12:08.126
for teens working
together on film or video.

00:12:08.126 --> 00:12:12.886
And it lets these teens easily
share files, give feedback,

00:12:13.246 --> 00:12:17.336
review clips, approve media,
and do a whole ton of stuff

00:12:17.336 --> 00:12:19.296
in that creative pro workflow.

00:12:19.296 --> 00:12:23.706
And it turns out that it's
really hard to do this right.

00:12:24.306 --> 00:12:28.116
And Frame.io nails it
by filling a big gap

00:12:28.116 --> 00:12:32.036
in the creator pro workflow by
solving this complicated task.

00:12:32.756 --> 00:12:35.186
And to give you a better
idea of how this app works,

00:12:35.486 --> 00:12:37.526
I'd like to ask Michael
to demo it to us now.

00:12:38.216 --> 00:12:38.746
>> Thank you, John.

00:12:39.296 --> 00:12:42.296
So this is a typical
project in Frame.io.

00:12:42.296 --> 00:12:45.496
Now it's really media-centric,
so you can see all the media

00:12:45.496 --> 00:12:47.576
in the lower half of the view.

00:12:48.046 --> 00:12:48.726
Now -- whoops.

00:12:50.286 --> 00:12:54.296
So basically what they've
done here is they've made a

00:12:54.296 --> 00:12:57.626
UICollectionViewFlowLayout
with UIKit dynamics,

00:12:57.946 --> 00:13:00.386
and that really makes
this view come alive.

00:13:00.386 --> 00:13:03.816
Now at the top, you can see
all the project participants.

00:13:04.266 --> 00:13:07.086
Now this is a really fun
and interactive animation.

00:13:07.916 --> 00:13:10.286
And that's really cool,
and I can do it slow.

00:13:10.286 --> 00:13:10.716
There we go.

00:13:10.776 --> 00:13:12.696
And that's using core animation

00:13:12.696 --> 00:13:14.076
with custom curves
and key frames.

00:13:14.416 --> 00:13:17.006
That opens up to a table
list view where I can swipe

00:13:17.326 --> 00:13:20.726
to remove someone from a project
or leave the project myself.

00:13:21.956 --> 00:13:25.556
Now the media player is
really key to Frame.io.

00:13:26.046 --> 00:13:28.696
And so what they've done here
is they've implemented 3D touch,

00:13:29.446 --> 00:13:30.956
and they've done this in a
number of different ways.

00:13:31.236 --> 00:13:33.126
The first one is a feature
they call Touch Scrub.

00:13:33.126 --> 00:13:37.986
So on this clip of this mountain
-- all I'm going to do is scrub

00:13:38.126 --> 00:13:40.046
across this clip very lightly.

00:13:40.046 --> 00:13:41.176
And you can see I
get an overview

00:13:41.176 --> 00:13:42.536
of the clip really quickly.

00:13:43.196 --> 00:13:45.036
Now the other thing that they've
done is they've gone deeper

00:13:45.036 --> 00:13:46.246
and implemented peak and pop.

00:13:46.396 --> 00:13:48.636
So on this clip, I'm
going to push gently.

00:13:48.756 --> 00:13:49.486
That peaks in.

00:13:49.936 --> 00:13:50.896
And now watch this.

00:13:50.896 --> 00:13:53.766
When I pop, it goes
